results.doc_title: [VIEW ONLY] F_ Meal & Add On Database
results.purpose: This spreadsheet tracks a meal database for a food service company, managing recipes, nutritional information, costs, dietary attributes, and operational details for meal preparation and delivery
key_data_points: Recipe IDs and MSKU codes for meal tracking
Cost data: meal costs ranging from $1.94-$3.69, max meal costs from $2.54-$4.85
L3 Run Ratings: 3.40-3.53 range with swap out percentages 0.65%-1.19%
Dietary attributes: Calorie Smart, Chef's Choice, High Protein, Dairy Free, Pork Free, Low Carb, Keto, GLP-1 Balance
Shelf life and plating dates tracked

entities.name: AS
entities.context: Chef's initials for Greek-Style Market Chicken Bowl and Red Pepper Bruschetta recipes

entities.name: SH
entities.context: Chef's initials for Garlic Tomato Cream Shredded Beef recipe

entities.name: Chicken & Mushroom Marsala
entities.context: Discontinued meal (Graveyard status) with 6 recipe variations (F00002A-F)

entities.name: Greek Isle Caper Salmon
entities.context: New menu item with European/Italian cuisine classification

entities.name: Greek-Style Market Chicken Bowl
entities.context: New menu item marked as Mediterranean and GLP-1 Support

entities.name: Red Pepper Bruschetta Shredded Chicken
entities.context: New menu item with Mediterranean classification

entities.name: Garlic Tomato Cream Shredded Beef
entities.context: New menu item with beef protein

insights: Product lifecycle management: 'Graveyard' status meals (Chicken & Mushroom Marsala variants) are being phased out while new meals are being introduced
Recipe versioning: Multiple cost variations exist for the same meal (F00002A-F), suggesting recipe optimization or ingredient substitution testing
Dietary trend focus: Strong emphasis on health-conscious options including GLP-1 Balance, Mediterranean diet, High Protein, and Calorie Smart categories
Protein diversity: Menu includes chicken (breast and shredded), salmon, and beef options with protein content ranging 27-44g per meal
Cost efficiency: New recipes ($2.36-$3.69) are competitively priced compared to discontinued items ($1.94-$2.27), suggesting value optimization
European/Italian cuisine dominance: All visible recipes are classified as European or Italian cuisine
Operational complexity: Meals require multiple preparation methods (marinade, brine, grill, oven, braiser, shredder) tracked for kitchen operations
Container standardization: All meals use '2 CT' containers with color-coded sleeves (Yellow, Blue, Red) for easy identification
Quality metrics: L3 Run Ratings and swap out percentages indicate customer satisfaction and meal replacement rates are actively monitored

results.purpose: Track outreach and interview coordination with food influencers across social media platforms

Follower counts range from 2,012 to 10.4 million
Multiple follow-up emails sent across phases
Influencer sizes: Micro (5K-100K), Mid (100K-500K), Macro (500K-1M), Mega (1M+)

insights: Low conversion rate: Only 1 interview secured out of 15 contacted (6.7% success rate)
4 outright rejections from contacted influencers (26.7% rejection rate)
Phase 5 outreach (4 influencers) yielded zero responses, all were Mega influencers with published cookbooks
Cookbook authors appear to be a target demographic - 11 influencers noted as published/upcoming authors
Geographic focus on US and Canada, with some European influencers (UK, Italy, Greece, Portugal, Austria)
Multi-platform presence is common - many influencers tracked across 2-3 platforms
Instagram is the dominant platform (32 influencers), followed by TikTok, YouTube, and Pinterest
Contact information varies widely - some have direct emails, others only social media or agency contacts
Larger influencers (Mega tier) tend to have lower response rates and use agency representation
The spreadsheet is actively being used with 5 distinct outreach phases, suggesting ongoing campaign

Multiple promo code campaigns: TURKEY, TRK, GBL, TRKXA series
Turkey promotion codes: ORGANIC TURKEY, TURKEY ACTIVATION NAE, TURKEY REACTIVATION NAE, TURKEY CODE 2023

entities.name: Good Chop

entities.name: ODL
entities.context: Referenced as source system for customer IDs and add-on column data

insights: Premium products (ribeyes, filet mignon, grass-fed beef) are offered as both lifetime and yearly promotions
Turkey-themed promotional campaigns appear to be a major marketing initiative with multiple code variants
Each voucher has standardized messaging: 'We've added your FREE [product]. Enjoy!'
Most promotions have 'Actives email banner' set to TRUE, indicating active email marketing campaigns
Customer IDs are organized by promo code type (TURKEY, TRK, GBL campaigns)
Product codes use abbreviations: BCN (Bacon), WNG (Wings), GFL (Ground Beef For Life), RFY (Ribeyes For Year), etc.
SKU index 108 is used for bacon, 147 for wings, suggesting standardized product catalog
Large list of customer IDs (60+) suggests significant promotional reach
